                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1063">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 367.112 Er 4/5.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the <gloss type="to">American Minister in temporary charge of the American
                            Embassy at Constantinople</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-12-05">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 5, 1910</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Should Erickson decide to return to Elbassan inform the Ottoman Government of his
                    itinerary and add that this Government will hold the Ottoman Government strictly
                    accountable for his safety and that of his family and property.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Adee.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
